came an apologist for apartheid.Drawing on personal interviews and extensive archival research, David H. Anthony has written much more than a biography of this enigmatic leader. In following the winding road of Yergan’s life, Anthony offers a tour through the complex and interrelated political and institutional movements that have shaped the history of the black world from the United States to South Africa.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAfrican American intellectualsvBiography. 0aAfrican American political activistsvBiography. 0aAfrican AmericansvBiography. 0aAfrican AmericansxPolitics and governmenty20th century. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Historical.2bisacsh  aBiography.  aYergan.  aabout.  aactivist.  ablack.  aintellectual.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081470704340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814707562423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814707562/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK